TradingAgents (Claude Code Plugin)
Copyright 2026 namikos

This product is a derivative work of and includes design ideas, agent role
definitions, and workflow patterns adapted from:

    TradingAgents: Multi-Agents LLM Financial Trading Framework
    https://github.com/TauricResearch/TradingAgents
    Copyright TauricResearch and contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

Specifically, the following parts of this plugin are inspired by or adapted
from the upstream project:

  - The agent role taxonomy (Fundamentals/Technical/News/Sentiment analyst,
    Bull/Bear researcher, Trader, Risk Manager).
  - The sequential workflow stages: parallel analyst research, bull/bear
    debate, trader synthesis, risk-manager approval.
  - The output convention `FINAL TRANSACTION PROPOSAL: **BUY/HOLD/SELL**`.
  - The system-prompt structure of each agent role (rewritten and adapted
    for Claude Code Agent Teams + MCP tools).

The native Claude Code orchestration (Agent Teams, mailbox messaging, plan
approval, MCP server, plugin packaging) is original to this project.

